This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses meta-learning algorithms for reinforcement learning. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing automated meta-learning algorithms. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses the application of meta-learning to reinforcement learning in the context of robotics and control systems. Finally, it may also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it discusses the use of unsupervised exploration techniques in meta-learning.
